The paper deals with synchronization and calibration protocols for distributed multiuser MIMO, which involves wireless communication, network architecture, and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of data communication and signal processing. The second likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), which deals with the design, implementation, and evaluation of computer networks. The third likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the analysis and control of complex systems. The fourth likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia), which deals with the processing, transmission, and storage of multimedia data. The fifth likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), which deals with the design, analysis, and implementation of distributed computing systems.
